  "text": "Salmonella typhimurium strains (virulent SL1344; attenuated aroA À SL7207) were used as described . Mice were infected i.v. with 1 3 10 6 colony-forming units (CFUs) SL7207 or 100 CFU SL1344. In vaccination and rechallenge experiments mice were first vaccinated with 1 3 10 6 CFU SL7207 and 90 days later were rechallenged i.v. with either 100 CFU SL1344 or 1 3 10 6 CFU SL7207, as indicated. In B cell depletion experiments, vaccinated C57BL/6 mice received a single i.v. dose of 250 mg anti-CD20 antibody (clone 18B12) 1 week prior to rechallenge with 100 CFU SL1344. The 18B12 IgG2a anti-CD20 was a kind gift of R. Dunn and M. Kehry at Biogen Idec [CITATION_1] . Survival was recorded daily and presented as percentage of live animals. We determined bacterial burden by plating dilutions of homogenized organs on MacConkey agar plates. Heat-killed Salmonella typhimurium (HKST) was SL1344 inactivated by incubation at 70 C for 1 hr.",
